1.Project Overview

ScholarStream is a full-stack MERN application designed to connect students with scholarship opportunities worldwide. Universities or organizations can post scholarships, while students can browse, search, and apply for them.
The platform streamlines the application and review process, allowing moderators and admins to manage applications efficiently.

Why this project?

Simplifies the process of finding financial aid for students.
Centralizes scholarship listings to ensure students don’t miss opportunities.
Enables admins to monitor and analyze platform data effectively.

2.Key Features

User Registration and Authentication (JWT + Google Social Login)
Role-based Access (Student, Moderator, Admin)
Scholarship Listing, Search, Filter, and Sorting
Scholarship Details with Reviews and Recommendations
Application System with status tracking (Pending → Processing → Completed)
Stripe Payment Integration for application fees
User Dashboards with role-specific views
Analytics dashboard for Admin (Charts & Metrics)
Responsive design with loading states and custom 404 page

3.Technologies Used

Frontend:
React.js
React Router
DaisyUI + Tailwind CSS
Framer Motion (Animations)

Backend:
Node.js
Express.js
MongoDB 
Firebase Admin (Authentication + Secure Config)
Stripe (Payment Integration)

Other Tools:
otenv (Environment variables)
JWT (Authentication & Authorization)
Axios (API Calls)

4.Data Design (MongoDB Collections)
Users Collection,
Scholarships Collection,
Applications Collection,
Reviews Collection.


5.Authentication & Security
JWT Token Verification for secure API calls
Role-based middleware: verifyAdmin and verifyModerator
Password validation on registration (minimum 6 chars, uppercase, special character)
Social Login (Google OAuth)
Environment variables for Firebase credentials, MongoDB credentials, and Stripe API keys

6.Pages & Layout

Public Pages:
Home Page (Top Scholarships, Hero Section, Animations)
All Scholarships Page (Search, Filter, Sort, Pagination)
Scholarship Details Page (Apply button, Reviews)
Login / Register Pages
404 Error Page

Private Pages (Dashboard):
Student Dashboard: My Applications, My Reviews, Pay / Delete / Edit Applications

Moderator Dashboard: Manage Applications, Add Feedback, Review Management

Admin Dashboard: Manage Users, Add/Edit/Delete Scholarships, Analytics

Shared Layouts:

Navbar (Logo, Home, All Scholarships, Login/Register, Profile dropdown)
Footer (Logo, Copyright, Social Media)

7.Payment System

Stripe Checkout Integration
Secure application fee payment
Payment status saved in Applications Collection
Payment Success / Failure Pages with proper redirects
Retry payment option available on Dashboard

8.Dashboard Layout

Admin:

User Management (Role change, Delete users)
Scholarship Management (Add/Edit/Delete scholarships)
Analytics (Total Users, Total Scholarships, Total Fees, Charts)

Moderator:

Manage all applications
Provide feedback
Update status (Processing / Completed / Rejected)
Moderate reviews

Student:

View profile
Manage personal applications
Edit or delete pending applications
Make payments
Add/Edit/Delete reviews




